title: California Counties Add Health Care For Immigrant Adults
text:
25 California Counties Add Health Care For Immigrant Adults 
NPR: A California county voted Tuesday to restore primary health care services to undocumented adults living in the county.Contra Costa County, east of San Francisco, joins 46 other California counties that have agreed to provide non-emergency care to immigrants who entered the country illegally.
